 Blood Bowl League for several years. For those of you not familiar, it is a Games Workshop/Warhammer tabletop creation. Think what a rugby/football match would be if played between Orcs and Wood Elves, or Halflings and the Undead, etc. Players can be killed, accumulate experience points, etc. I was never exposed to AD&amp;D as a youth, but the friends I play BB with had/have an exhaustive campaign on the old Greyhawk world. This game can be played by writing names on a roster and playing, but we have taken it several steps deeper, including writeups on the lives of our players, their personalities and background, etc. It is set in the old D&amp;D Greyhawk world. We started this league in 1996, and when these guys get killed (it does happen in-game) there are times we have to halt the game for a a few minutes to take it in. My point here is that my friends and I don't just heap our players with the best skills as they gain experience, we try to think about what would make sense for the character as well. A hard bitten human lineman, a former combat infantry sargent with a nasty disposition and a mother hen mentality toward his players would not acquire a side-step agility skill for example. So it is possible to RP in any environment. I role play an enthusiastic employee here at work, for another example.<br><br>3) Lite Brite, good call, didn't know they still made them!  <p>Palantiri, Ranger of Norrath<BR>Sacred Jesters Of Quellious, Woodfellas<BR>Cosmos Mariner, Destination Unknown<BR>www.angelfire.com/games2/NNB/ <BR><BR>Dohneagle of Firiona Vie<BR><BR>Why is it that every MOB you are hunting is never found unless you are on a corpse run, when they are at every turn?<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <fon